1 AN ACT relating to appropriations providing financing and conditions for the
2 operations, maintenance, support, and functioning of the Transportation Cabinet of the
3 Commonwealth of Kentucky.
4 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
5 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet Budget is as follows:
6 PART I
7 OPERATING BUDGET
8 (1) Funds Appropriations: There is appropriated out of the General Fund, Road
9 Fund, Restricted Funds accounts, or Federal Funds accounts for the fiscal year beginning
10 July 1, 2025 and ending June 30, 2026, for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2026, and
11 ending June 30, 2027, and for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2027, and ending June 30,
12 2028, the following discrete sums, or so much thereof as may be necessary. Appropriated
13 funds are included pursuant to KRS 48.700 and 48.710. Each appropriation is made by
14 source of respective fund or funds accounts. Appropriations for the budget units of the
15 Transportation Cabinet are subject to the provisions of Chapters 12, 42, 45, and 48 of the
16 Kentucky Revised Statutes and compliance with the conditions and procedures set forth
17 in this Act.
